<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-7">
    <div class="row">

      <!-- header line -->
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-danger btn-lg navigation" ng-click="exit()">
          Cancel
        </button>  
        <h3 class="wizard-title">
          Print Bed Leveling
        </h3>
        <br/>&nbsp;
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 1 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '1'">
        <p>The following steps will guide you through the process of leveling the
          print bed. This is necessary to achieve best print results and lay down a perfect
          first layer that bonds firmly to the print surface</p>
        <p>Please confirm:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A clean printbed is installed.</li>
          <li>The nozzle tips are cleaned from any print material residue
            (gently remove any material with tweezers).</li>
          <li>No Filament is loaded in the right extruder.</li>        
        </ul>
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step2()">
          OK, continue
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 2 -->
      <div class="col-md-12" ng-show="step == '2'">
        <p>Please wait while the print bed is beeing preheated. This may take a couple of minutes.</p>
        <p>Current print bed temperature: <b>{{ bed_temp }}Â°C</b></p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step1()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right {{ !bed_preheated && 'disabled' }} btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step3()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 3 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '3'"> 
        <p>Now loosen the two set screws on the <b>right</b> extruder barrel.</p>
        <p><b>WARNING: Carefully check if extruder is still hot before touching the nozzle!.</b></p>
        <p>Then slide the right extruder barrel up to make sure the right nozzle tip is a bit higher 
          than the left tip.</p>    
        <br/>
        <br/>    
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step2()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step5()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 5 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '5'">
        <p>Next, loosen all <b>three</b> print bed leveling thumb screws a bit (as shown to the right).</p>
        <p>The print bed must be able to easily slide up and down against the spring suspension.</p>
        <p>In the following the print head will move to three leveling positions one after another
          and push the print bed down some millimeters.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step3()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step6()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>      

      <!-- text contents step 6 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '6'">
        <p>Position 1:</p>
        <p>After the movement gently fasten the bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>front</b>.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step5()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step7()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>      

      <!-- text contents step 7 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '7'">
        <p>Position 2:</p>
        <p>After the movement gently fasten the bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>right</b> side.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step6()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step8()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 8 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '8'">
        <p>Position 3:</p>
        <p>After the movement gently fasten the bed leveling thumb screw on the <b>left</b> side.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step7()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step9()">
          Next
        </button>     
      </div>

      <!-- text contents step 9 -->
      <div class="col-md-7" ng-show="step == '9'">
        <p>The print bed is leveled now.</p>
        <p>Finally, slide the <b>right</b> extruder barrel back down until it just
          touches the print bed and gently tighten the two set screws again.</p>
        <p>That's it, you are done.</p>
        <br/>
        <br/>  
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg navigation" ng-click="step8()">
          Back
        </button>         
        <button type="button" class="pull-right btn btn-primary btn-lg navigation" ng-click="exit()">
          Done!
        </button>     
      </div>      

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- image step 1 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '1'">
    <!-- picture: cleaning nozzle with tweezers -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_tweezers.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">
  </div>  

  <!-- image step 2 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '2'">
    <!-- picture: printbed in preheat-position -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_preheat.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">    
  </div> 

  <!-- image step 3 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '3'">
    <!-- picture: barrel set screws-->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_barrelscrews.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">    
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 5 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '5'">
    <!-- picture: unscrew leveling bolts -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_thumbscrews.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">    
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 6 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '6'">
    <!-- picture: fasten front thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_bedfront.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 7 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '7'">
    <!-- picture: fasten right thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_bedright.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">
  </div>   

  <!-- image step 8 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '8'">
    <!-- picture: fasten left thumbscrew -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_bedleft.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">
  </div>

  <!-- image step 9 -->
  <div class="col-md-5" ng-show="step == '9'">
    <!-- picture: fasten barrel -->
    <img src="<%= asset_path("touchapp/images/wizard_leveling_rightnozzle.jpg") %>" class="img-responsive">
  </div> 

</div>
